Key Match Events: Royce Lewis hit a deep fly ball to center field that appeared to clear the wall for a grand slam, but review revealed the ball hit the top of the padding, resulting in a two-run double that gave the Twins a 6-3 lead.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Angels had three hits and a run off Duran in the ninth inning, but he was able to close it out and pick up his 23rd save of the year.
Sands picked up his seventh win of the year for the Twins.
